But for trans developers in the game industry, that's not

00:19:50.910 --> 00:19:52.160
a niche concern, right?

00:19:52.160 --> 00:19:53.140
That's their name.

00:19:53.140 --> 00:19:54.100
It's important.

00:19:54.100 --> 00:19:58.900
And right now, getting a credit updated in a shipped game

00:19:58.910 --> 00:20:02.020
is a nightmare of bureaucracy and platform policies.

00:20:02.020 --> 00:20:05.240
With developer-controlled credits on protocol, it's an update

00:20:05.240 --> 00:20:07.680
to a record owned by that contributor.

00:20:07.770 --> 00:20:12.300
Somebody else started talking about player-owned save data, cloud

00:20:12.300 --> 00:20:12.750
saves.

00:20:12.750 --> 00:20:14.820
And this one's a little personal for me.

00:20:14.820 --> 00:20:18.240
City of Heroes, some of you may remember, it was

00:20:18.240 --> 00:20:22.130
a really popular MMO, massively multiplayer online game, owned

